==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: octet
<hw>oc*tet"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From L.
<ets>octo</ets> eight, like E. <ets>duet</ets>, fr.L. <ets>duo</ets>.
See <er>Octave</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A
composition for eight parts, usually for eight solo instruments or
voices.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A group of eight singers or eight
musicians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Octic</ent>⟦br⟧
